      },
      {
        "step_no": 2,
        "text": "Prepare aromatics and vegetables: While rice cooks, thinly slice shallot, mince garlic, grate ginger, and slice the red bell pepper; set herbs and garnishes aside.",
        "time_min": 6
      },
      {
        "step_no": 3,
        "text": "Heat oil in a large skillet or wok over medium-high heat until shimmering; add shallot and saut√© until translucent, then add garlic and ginger and cook briefly until fragrant.",
        "time_min": 2
      },
      {
        "step_no": 4,
        "text": "Add red curry paste to the aromatics and fry, stirring constantly, for about 1 minute to bloom the spices and deepen the flavor.",
        "time_min": 1
      },
      {
        "step_no": 5,
        "text": "Pour in coconut milk, stir to combine with the paste, bring to a gentle simmer, then add fish sauce and brown sugar; taste and adjust seasoning for balance of savory, sweet and salty.",
        "time_min": 2
      },
      {
        "step_no": 6,
        "text": "Add sliced red bell pepper to the simmering coconut curry and cook until just tender-crisp, about 2 minutes.",
        "time_min": 2
      },
      {
        "step_no": 7,
        "text": "Add shrimp to the curry in a single layer, simmer gently until shrimp are opaque and just cooked through, turning once; this should take only a few minutes depending on size.",
        "time_min": 3
      },
      {
        "step_no": 8,
        "text": "Finish the curry by stirring in lime juice and chopped thai basil; adjust heat with crushed red pepper if desired and remove from heat.",
        "time_min": 1
      },
      {
        "step_no": 9,
        "text": "Plate: Fluff the cooked jasmine rice with a fork, divide among bowls or plates, spoon the shrimp coconut curry over the rice, and garnish with cilantro and sliced green onions.",
